{{ 'drye-mechanics-glove-intro.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<section class="dryeNEW-section mech-glove-intro" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="dryeNEW-container">
    <div class="mech-glove-intro__grid">

      <div class="mech-glove-intro__media">
        {% if section.settings.image != blank %}
          {% assign mech_glove_intro_alt = section.settings.image_alt | escape %}
          {{
            section.settings.image
            | image_url: width: 1400
            | image_tag: class: 'mech-glove-intro__image', loading: 'lazy', alt: mech_glove_intro_alt
          }}
        {% else %}
          <div class="mech-glove-intro__media-placeholder"></div>
        {% endif %}
      </div>

      <div class="mech-glove-intro__text">
        {% if section.settings.eyebrow != blank %}
          <span class="dryeNEW-micro">{{ section.settings.eyebrow }}</span>
        {% endif %}

        {% if section.settings.heading != blank %}
          <h2 class="dryeNEW-h2 mech-glove-intro__heading">
            {{ section.settings.heading }}
          </h2>
        {% endif %}

        {% if section.settings.subheading != blank %}
          <div class="mech-glove-intro__subheading">
            {{ section.settings.subheading }}
          </div>
        {% endif %}

        {% if section.settings.body != blank %}
          <div class="dryeNEW-body mech-glove-intro__body">
            {{ section.settings.body }}
          </div>
        {% endif %}
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "DRYE Mechanics Glove",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image",
      "label": "Image"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "image_alt",
      "label": "Image alt text",
      "default": "Macro photograph of DRYE's dual-layer textile showing moisture transport through the fabric structure."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "Pressure-driven moisture transport"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "A liner built for sealed gloves — not open air."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "subheading",
      "label": "Subheading",
      "default": "0.4mm thin. No chemicals. No coatings. Fits inside any work glove."
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>Every fabric you've ever worn under gloves — cotton, merino, polyester, silk — works by <strong>absorbing moisture and releasing it into the air</strong>. That's fine outside. Inside a sealed glove, there is no air. The fabric saturates. The moisture has nowhere to go.</p><p>DRYE doesn't absorb on the skin side. The inner layer is hydrophobic polypropylene — it <strong>cannot</strong> hold moisture. The outer layer is hydrophilic Lyocell, which pulls moisture continuously outward through the thickness of the fabric.</p><p>The transport is driven by the structure itself. <strong>The harder you work, the more your glove compresses the fabric, the faster it moves.</strong> No saturation point. No stopping point. It's the only textile mechanism that gets stronger under pressure instead of collapsing.</p>"
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "DRYE Mechanics Glove"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}